  "description": {
    "en": {
      "provenance": "imported",
      "value": "The overall objective of the South-South Cooperation between the Government of China (GoC), Government of Nepal (GoN) and UNFPA is to improve maternal and women’s health in Nepal through strengthened disaster preparedness and response capacity in addressing the reproductive health needs of women and girls, including midwifery capacities for quality maternal health care. In order to achieve this objective, an agreement was signed to undertake critical interventions with a longer-term vision to strengthen South-South Cooperation initiatives under the 8th UNFPA Country Programme of Cooperation in China , and in line with the principles and objectives of the Government of China’s Belt and Road Initiative."
    },
